      "lineNumber": 1,
      "text": "March 19, 1969",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 2,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 3,
      "text": "John Edgar Hoover",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 4,
      "text": "United States Department of Justice",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 5,
      "text": "Federal Bureau of Investigation",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 6,
      "text": "Washington 25, D.C.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 7,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "text": "See 14-2488-6[unclear]",
      "status": "needs_image_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "Dear Mr. Hoover:",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "December 7, 1963, I observed in the sky at Moorestown, New Jersey, an",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "unusual object and its unusual behavior. On December 8, 1963, just",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "text": "24 hours later at Elkton, Maryland, the Pan American Aircraft with 73",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "passengers and a crew of eight perished when this aircraft exploded in",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "mid air and crashed.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "I sent a tape recording of the observation I had made on December 7,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "text": "to Mr. J. Edgar Hoover and associated this object with the crash of",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "this plane. Mr. Hoover informed me that the Civil Aeronautics Board",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "was investigating this disaster and what I had sent to him would be",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "forwarded to them, the C.A.B.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "text": "In the month of March, 1965, the C.A.B., released a report that this",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "accident and cause was due to a lightning strike.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "I protested to Senator Case of New Jersey. Senator Case mailed me",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "text": "the official report by the C.A.B., along with a letter by a Mr.",
      "status": "pending_image_audit"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "[REDACTED], Director Community and Congressional Relations.",
      "status": "redaction_marker_check"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "Upon reading the Official C.A.B. report on this accident and also",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "this letter I have come to the conclusion that neither the C.A.B. or",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "the writer of this letter know what they are talking about and have",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "text": "missed the point completely.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "I claimed that the object which I seen was laying air mines and",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "that this aircraft was destroyed by contact with one of these mines.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "To substantiate my claim I would refer you to page 8 line 20 to line",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "24 inclusive of this report File #1-0015. Boeing 707-121 N709PA Pan",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "American World Airways, Inc., near Elkton, Maryland, December 8,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "1963.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
